  <span id="freeText4439007929576965604" style="display:none">4+<br />Read these 11 stories over a couple of weeks and it was a blissful experience!<br /><br />A great collection of short stories, because:<br />1. They are not very short (30-40 pages each)<br />2. Characters criss cross in each others stories.<br />So in effect, felt this was a good novel impersonating as short stories. <br /><br />Mistry's story-telling techniques are at an altogether different level.<br />This one focuses on human emotions and observations from middle class Parsi families living in a building called Firozsha Baag.<br /><br />This was my second book (first was AFB), and I've become a fan of the author.<br />Highly recommended.</span>
