          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1290239245" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14155004784396655943">Minus the obvious references to a specific community, the stories can belong to anyone who has lived a life in a (cramped) apartment complex. The dynamics between people is what makes this collection stand out. They all have couple of things in common - self actualization and a bittersweet ending.<br/><br/>Mistry has a wonderful way in transcending human nature into words. This wasn&apos;t a fun read. The stories are about people we have known in our lives. An uncle here, an aunty there, a friend&apos;s relative on</span>
  <span id="freeText14155004784396655943" style="display:none">Minus the obvious references to a specific community, the stories can belong to anyone who has lived a life in a (cramped) apartment complex. The dynamics between people is what makes this collection stand out. They all have couple of things in common - self actualization and a bittersweet ending.<br /><br />Mistry has a wonderful way in transcending human nature into words. This wasn't a fun read. The stories are about people we have known in our lives. An uncle here, an aunty there, a friend's relative on the side...they are in our midst. And that's what makes this seemingly simplistic collection, achy in all the right places :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="14155004784396655943" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

