<div id="review_3931832357" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3931832357" />
    <a title="Jerry Pogan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/59682834-jerry-pogan"><img alt="Jerry Pogan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607708953p2/59682834.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3931832357?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jerry Pogan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jerry Pogan" href="/user/show/59682834-jerry-pogan">Jerry Pogan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3931832357" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9794742588010097413">A very good collection of short stories by Rohinton Mistry an author who wrote three extremely good books several years ago but, apparently, nothing since. This is an older book first published in 1987. The stories in this book are satirical studies of various aspects of Indian culture all based in an apartment complex in Bombay and involving several recurring characters. Some of the better stories are: Auspicious Occasion that exposes much about the Firozsha Baag apartments and their decaying c</span>
  <span id="freeText9794742588010097413" style="display:none">A very good collection of short stories by Rohinton Mistry an author who wrote three extremely good books several years ago but, apparently, nothing since. This is an older book first published in 1987. The stories in this book are satirical studies of various aspects of Indian culture all based in an apartment complex in Bombay and involving several recurring characters. Some of the better stories are: Auspicious Occasion that exposes much about the Firozsha Baag apartments and their decaying condition as well as a man with constipation, Condolence Visit about a newly widowed woman and the expectations placed on her, The Collectors about a very shy young boy (who is featured in other stories) and his friendship with a man who gets him started in stamp collecting, Squatter about a young man who emigrated to Toronto and his inability to adapt to a sit down toilet and Exercisers about a shy young man of nineteen (the same boy from The Collectors) who has his first girlfriend against his parents wishes. These were all very entertaining stories and a window into Indian culture.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9794742588010097413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


